CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: Body wraps tattered by sharp, thorny vines.

Description.LocalizedString: A dark cape covering a dress suit, fastened with a mutilated angel that inspires both fear and respectability.
Did the roots grow out of him, or up from the earth?
Garbs taken from those who ventured too far from their home.
He has been wearing this old and tattered clothing for a while.
Rusted steel weaves and slices along his body, sharp edges scraping with each movement. It was the same fate as the victims he fed into the crusher, though they had been granted the mercy of death.
Rusted steel from an old vehicle abandoned in the swamp covered his flesh.
What was once good and pure now burned as an inferno within him. So hot, it would someday leave nothing but cold, dry ash.
What good is gold when your spirit is dead?
Extremely easy to see, except for when it isn’t.
Extremely easy to see, except for when it’s foggy.

Description.LocalizedString: Wart-covered vest and waist wraps that move nimbly through pools of water and blood.
A once fine cloak now caked in the offal of his prey.

Description.LocalizedString: Embrace the cold, dark caress of the shadows for they are your only refuge.

CollectionDescription.LocalizedString: A traditional dress wrap worn during rituals. It is held up by an ornate, decorative belt.
A crippled heart thumping faintly against the hollowed trunk of its withered breastbone.

Description.LocalizedString: A pale, crusted mask that conceals a dead, yellowed-fleshed face that no one dared to love. Until, perhaps…
A half-mask that fails to conceal the evil within.
A burlap sack with short sticks where the brain should be.
A sturdy mask made of bark that allowed him to venture in the woods undetected.
He blended in with the fog, with his pale and rough skin.
He returned from the spirit world, changed. The metal chains and plates fused into him, as if memories of his former life as a wrecker fused with his physical form.
He sought vengeance for his unjust fate as he waded through dirty water. Leathery fabric scraped the scales of his withered leather cloak.
Somewhere beneath the hood is conflict, uncertainty, and—most of all—rage.
The twin growths that burst from his skull caused a pain he could never forget.
While he should probably have had his helmet on, the sweltering heat made it worth taking a risk from time to time.
While he should probably have had his helmet on, the unending trials made it worth taking a risk from time to time.

A crown crafted for a very special anniversary.

A reptilian spine of decomposing flesh made from his previous kills.
A vicious weapon pieced together with refuse from the scrap heap, and the skull of a man who deserved everything he got.
